{"department_text": "Automotive & Industrial", "nr_products": 9719, "catid": 342, "level": 0, "url": "http://www.amazon.com/s/ref=lp_318135011_nr_n_3?rh=n%3A16310091%2Cn%3A%2116310161%2Cn%3A318135011%2Cn%3A1265106011&bbn=318135011&ie=UTF8&qid=1395833212&rnid=318135011", "text": "Lockout & Tagout Products", "description_title": "Lock Out Tag Out", "parent_url": "http://www.amazon.com/b/ref=sd_allcat_ind_saf/178-6146972-2884157?ie=UTF8&node=318135011", "keyword_count": {"lock": 22, "tag": 22, "lock out tag": 4}, "description_wc": 269, "description_text": "Lock out tag out, sometimes referred to as lockout tagout (LO/TO), are safety procedures that use safety devices and tags to help keep areas and people safe in research, industry, and other environments. Lock out tag out devices use color, warning labels or tags, and a physical barrier to alert people, temporarily prohibit machine operation or power activation, and reduce accidents, during maintenance or repair. A lockout tagout tag attaches to a locked device and provides instructions and information. Lockout tagout products can include safety devices that may require lock out tag out security, such as a circuit breaker, valves, plugs, cylinder tanks, gas cylinders, and an adjustable gate valve lockout tagout. A lockout tagout hasp or folding lockout scissors clamp can help provide lockout tagout security. Lockout tagout devices can come in kits that provide the ability to use lockout tagout procedures for multiple areas. Lockout tagout accessories include a clip board, belt pouch, safety tag station, lockout tagout holder, lock box, binders to hold sheets of lockout tagout procedures, a lockout station that may be wall-mounted, and a compliance center that can include zippered binders and mounting brackets. Lockout tagout procedures are commonly applied in energy source environments such as electrical, mechanical, chemical, pneumatic, hydraulic, and thermal energy. Lockout tagout security procedures may also apply in construction, agriculture, maritime, or oil and gas drilling and servicing industries. When working with hazardous energy, lock out tag out procedures are also known as isolation procedures. Lockout tagout procedures can meet standards such as Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA), and Canadian Standards Association (CSA).", "parent_text": "Safety", "parent_catid": 167, "keyword_density": {"lock": "8.3", "tag": "8.3", "lock out tag": "4.5"}, "department_id": 15},
{"department_text": "Automotive & Industrial", "nr_products": 253695, "catid": 343, "level": 0, "url": "http://www.amazon.com/s/ref=lp_318135011_nr_n_4?rh=n%3A16310091%2Cn%3A%2116310161%2Cn%3A318135011%2Cn%3A486555011&bbn=318135011&ie=UTF8&qid=1395833212&rnid=318135011", "text": "Personal Protective Equipment", "description_title": "PPE from Amazon.com", "parent_url": "http://www.amazon.com/b/ref=sd_allcat_ind_saf/178-6146972-2884157?ie=UTF8&node=318135011", "keyword_count": {"amazoncom": 2, "ppe from amazoncom": 1, "ppe": 7}, "description_wc": 319, "description_text": "Whether you work construction or you\u2019re a hobby do-it-yourself-er, you are your most valuable asset in getting the job done. Without you, who would weld the right pipes together, build the forms you need to pour concrete, or dig out foundations? We know personal protective equipment, or PPE, is as important a tool as your welding rods, shovels, hammers or wrenches. That\u2019s why Amazon.com carries all the PPE you need to protect yourself on the job. Labor laws require that all workers wear the appropriate PPE to counter the specific hazards of each worksite. We offer a wide selection of protective glasses and goggles can keep flying debris, chemicals, and hazardous fumes out of your eyes. Our polarized, UV-protective sunglasses guard your eyes from overexposure to the sun while also deflecting flying particles. Filter your search by average customer rating to browse the most appropriate and customer-tested PPE first. We also have a variety of work gloves for every job, including latex, leather, fingerless, and welding gloves. Whether you need to protect against pinching and grinding, bruising, cuts and lacerations, dangerous chemicals, or flying sparks, we have the right PPE for you. Our utility gloves are built with quality materials and fit, well, like a glove. Their slim design prevents the ends of the fingers from bunching up when you have to do fine, detailed work. Hard hats are crucial for worker safety in areas where dropping objects, swinging tools, and other hazards exist. We have cap-style hard hats and full-brimmed hard hats to suit your job. We also carry a variety of other PPE, including ear-plugs to protect your hearing in loud areas, safety vests for visibility, fall arrest kits, and neck protectors to save your neck from constant UV exposure. You are too important to risk injury or harm. Keep yourself protected with the PPE from Amazon.com.", "parent_text": "Safety", "parent_catid": 167, "keyword_density": {"amazoncom": "0.6", "ppe from amazoncom": "0.9", "ppe": "2.2"}, "department_id": 15},
