{"department_text": "Home, Garden & Tools", "nr_products": 41444, "catid": 753, "level": 0, "url": "http://www.amazon.com/s/ref=lp_511228_nr_n_13?rh=n%3A228013%2Cn%3A%21468240%2Cn%3A511228%2Cn%3A511388&bbn=511228&ie=UTF8&qid=1395833317&rnid=511228", "text": "Tarps & Tie-Downs", "department_url": "http://www.amazon.com/s/ref=lp_284507_ex_n_1?rh=n%3A1055398&bbn=1055398&ie=UTF8&qid=1393338782", "description_title": "Tarps from Amazon.com", "parent_url": "http://www.amazon.com/Hardware-Locks-and-Fasteners/b/ref=sd_allcat_hdw/178-6146972-2884157?ie=UTF8&node=511228", "keyword_count": {"tarps from amazoncom": 1, "amazoncom": 2, "tarps": 6}, "description_wc": 320, "description_text": "Even if it\u2019s raining outside, you can stay dry under your very own blue sky by setting up convenient and waterproof tarps. At Amazon.com, you\u2019ll find tarps of all kinds, from heavy duty, extra thick work tarps, to smaller recreational tarps suitable for light home use. To protect things like wood piles that need to stay dry and protected over long periods of time, it\u2019s important to use a coated, heavy duty tarp that will effectively stand up to the wind, rain, and sun. Rust-resistant grommets, UV protection, and thick, durable construction will all help your tarp work better and longer. For light duty jobs around the yard, a thinner, less expensive tarp will be more than enough. You don\u2019t have to cancel outdoor parties and barbecues, even if you see the clouds rolling in. Keep the party going and keep your guests dry by stringing up a tarp for shelter. You can also save yourself cold toes and a wet bed on camping trips by pitching your tent on a tarp to keep moisture from seeping in. Many products feature detailed descriptions of their weight, size, and color, so you can quickly find a tarp that suits your needs. Don\u2019t forget the tie downs, twine, bungee cords, and rope you need to set up your tarp. We offer a huge variety of fasteners and accessories for tarps, so you\u2019ll save time shopping online for all your gear. Most pickup truck owners know the value of a solid tarp and a few good ratchet straps. Securing your load is crucial for safety on the road, and we make it easy to be sure you\u2019ve got everything you need to stay covered. Keep valuables you store outside dry and protected, secure a load in a pickup, or keep your tent of the dirt on a camping trip with sturdy, waterproof tarps from Amazon.com.", "parent_text": "Hardware", "parent_catid": 118, "keyword_density": {"tarps from amazoncom": "0.9", "amazoncom": "0.6", "tarps": "1.9"}, "department_id": 10},
