{"department_text": "Electronics & Computers", "nr_products": 23888, "catid": 826, "level": 0, "url": "http://www.amazon.com/s/ref=lp_11091801_nr_n_0?rh=n%3A11091801%2Cn%3A%2111965861%2Cn%3A11971241&bbn=11965861&ie=UTF8&qid=1395833355&rnid=11965861", "text": "Guitars", "department_url": "http://www.amazon.com/s/ref=lp_172659_ex_n_1?rh=n%3A172282&bbn=172282&ie=UTF8&qid=1393338741", "description_title": "Guitars from Amazon.com", "parent_url": "http://www.amazon.com/musical-instruments-accessories-sound-recording/b/ref=sd_allcat_mi/178-6146972-2884157?ie=UTF8&node=11091801", "keyword_count": {"amazoncom": 2, "guitars": 9}, "description_wc": 378, "description_text": "There\u2019s nothing like new gear to help you get excited about making music. Guitars that want to be picked up and played will motivate you to learn licks faster, write riffs better, and become a more creative musician. If you\u2019re fingering your first chords, or recording your follow up album, your guitars and amps should inspire you to practice and play at your best. From dreadnoughts to parlors, you\u2019ll find acoustic guitars in a huge variety of styles at Amazon.com. We carry popular brands like Martin, Taylor, and Takamine, so no matter what look and feel you\u2019re going for, there\u2019s an acoustic to suit your style. Our product filters can help you track down the perfect instrument. Browse guitars by brand, layout, and even top, back, or neck woods. For warm, folky sounds, many players prefer mahogany, while maple has a brighter, punchy tone. From Chuck Berry to Jack white, electric guitar has been the backbone of rock and roll for decades. Legendary guitars like the Gibson Les Paul and Fender Stratocaster have appeared on countless #1 records, and remain a popular choice today. The variety of options for electric guitars is practically endless. Humbuckers, single coils, Floyd Rose tremolos, and dozens of other features mean there\u2019s an instrument fit for every player. We make it easy to find guitars you\u2019re interested in. Choose the brands, features, and colors you\u2019re interested in, and we\u2019ll show you guitars that match your criteria. All the amplifiers and accessories you need to get the most out of your tone are available at Amazon.com. Our range of amp selection, from 5-watt practice amps and all-tube amps to 100-watt full stacks and everything in between, will have you strumming and shredding to your heart\u2019s content. Whether you\u2019re after a gritty, British tone, or a clean and sparkly American shimmer, we\u2019ve got amps from popular brands like Marshall, Vox, and Fender to help you find the perfect sound. For new guitar players and old pros alike, the excitement of trying out new gear can motivate you creatively and technically. Explore your tone, style, and imagination with guitars and guitar accessories that make you want to grow as a player.", "parent_text": "Musical Instruments", "parent_catid": 94, "keyword_density": {"amazoncom": "0.5", "guitars": "2.4"}, "department_id": 9},
{"department_text": "Electronics & Computers", "nr_products": 3334, "catid": 827, "level": 0, "url": "http://www.amazon.com/s/ref=lp_11091801_nr_n_1?rh=n%3A11091801%2Cn%3A%2111965861%2Cn%3A11971311&bbn=11965861&ie=UTF8&qid=1395833355&rnid=11965861", "text": "Bass Guitars", "department_url": "http://www.amazon.com/s/ref=lp_172659_ex_n_1?rh=n%3A172282&bbn=172282&ie=UTF8&qid=1393338741", "description_title": "Bass Guitars from Amazon.com", "parent_url": "http://www.amazon.com/musical-instruments-accessories-sound-recording/b/ref=sd_allcat_mi/178-6146972-2884157?ie=UTF8&node=11091801", "keyword_count": {"amazoncom": 1, "bass guitars": 5, "bass": 14}, "description_wc": 355, "description_text": "Electric bass guitars have been the foundation of the rock, funk, and R&B sound for decades. Legends like Geddy Lee, Bootsy Collins, and Flea defined and redefined what was possible with only four strings on every album they released. Holding down the bottom end is no small task, so make sure your bass and amp give you all the low frequency thunder you need to shake up the crowd all night long. When Leo Fender released the Precision Bass in 1951, no one could have guessed how far reaching of an impact it would have. Bass players were able to compete with drummers and horn sections for volume, and whole new genres of music emerged. A lot has changed since then, however. Bass guitars with active electronics, exotic wood bodies, and 5 or more strings are common, giving modern bass players have unprecedented control over their sound. You\u2019ll find bass guitars with from Fender, Gibson, Warwick, and other top brands at Amazon.com. Our product filters make it easy to browse basses you\u2019re interested in. Just choose the brands, colors, and even number of strings you want, and we\u2019ll show you instruments that fit your style and sound. Are you looking for a new way to supercharge your tone? Bass guitars that are equipped with active pickups like the EMG-P humbucker have highly articulated high-end response, combined with a powerful low end, and virtually no unwanted feedback. Whether you\u2019re going for a warm, tube-driven vintage vibe, or a heavy modern sound, choosing the right bass amp is crucial to getting the most out of your bass guitar\u2019s tone. Classic amp makers like Ampeg deliver all the 1970s authenticity and charm you could want from a bass amp, while newer manufacturers like Genz Benz and Gallien-Kreuger can get you more watts per dollar than ever before. Behind every guitar solo, epic vocal performance, and catchy keyboard hook, there\u2019s a solid wall of thick, groovy bass propping it all up. Make the most of your sound with bass guitars and amps that maximize your rumble and roar.", "parent_text": "Musical Instruments", "parent_catid": 94, "keyword_density": {"amazoncom": "0.3", "bass guitars": "2.8", "bass": "3.9"}, "department_id": 9},
{"department_text": "Electronics & Computers", "nr_products": 23790, "catid": 828, "level": 0, "url": "http://www.amazon.com/s/ref=lp_11091801_nr_n_2?rh=n%3A11091801%2Cn%3A%2111965861%2Cn%3A11970241&bbn=11965861&ie=UTF8&qid=1395833355&rnid=11965861", "text": "Drums & Percussion", "department_url": "http://www.amazon.com/s/ref=lp_172659_ex_n_1?rh=n%3A172282&bbn=172282&ie=UTF8&qid=1393338741", "description_title": "Drums from Amazon.com", "parent_url": "http://www.amazon.com/musical-instruments-accessories-sound-recording/b/ref=sd_allcat_mi/178-6146972-2884157?ie=UTF8&node=11091801", "keyword_count": {"amazoncom": 2, "drums": 9}, "description_wc": 420, "description_text": "Percussion instruments are the most ancient instruments of all, and were present in the early tribal days of nearly every civilization. Drums today are an important part of human culture, not just because they speak to a variety of musical heritages, but because it\u2019s said we all carry around a personal rhythm in our beating hearts. At Amazon.com, we honor one of the world\u2019s oldest traditions by offering drums and percussion accessories for every level of player. Looking for complete drum sets for the drummer in your life? You\u2019ll feel like a king when you sit at the throne of a new five-piece drum set from one of the industry\u2019s most popular brands, such as Pearl, Tama, Mapex, and more. We even offer all the extra bells and whistles so you can start rocking away. Find all the drum accessories you need, from double bass pedals, cymbals, and triangles, to replacement drum heads, drum stools, and stands. When you need more cow bell, or your intense, gut-busting, around-the-world drum fills break the heads off of your sticks, be sure to stock up on replacement sticks and other drum accessories. If you\u2019re looking for more traditional hand drums, you can travel the world with our assortment of hand drums from all over the world. Djembes are rich-sounding, African drums that can produce a variety of tones. Check out our selection of doumbeks, Arabic drums, usually made of metal, that provide crisp, melodic cracks and pops. Hand drums and other handheld percussions, like tambourines and shakers, are great for impromptu jam sessions and for kids to learn basic rhythms. Our bongos are fun for reliving the glory of the beat poets of the 1950s, or for a foray into the lively musical traditions of salsa, son, or samba. Electronic drum sets provide a great way to practice without rattling the whole house. These sets provide volume control so you won\u2019t wake up the neighbors, but you can also plug in headphones to achieve a very quiet percussion session. That way only you will feel the noise. Electronic drums make ideal beginning sets, so students who are a little shy to practice out loud can just play to themselves. An extra benefit of electric drum sets is that some come equipped with built-in metronomes to keep you on time. Drum up a little inspiration and vigor--and keep the beat going on--with all the drums and percussion instruments from Amazon.com.", "parent_text": "Musical Instruments", "parent_catid": 94, "keyword_density": {"amazoncom": "0.5", "drums": "2.1"}, "department_id": 9},
